annotation.TEXT: Argh, I've gotta memorize what to do on each new screen...
Looks like that terminal will be my ticket out of here. But, I didn't get any new keycards in this area, so where will I go next?
Man, this is harder than it looks.
D'oh, I overshot there.
Well, that didn't take too many tries, fortunately, and uncaging those squares didn't make them a hazard that I had to worry about dodging.

Yes! Fortunately, this wasn't nearly as bad as that one trinket in Golden Spiral! (Yes, I'm going to keep referencing that one.) Alright, now I assume the warp takes me back, but what's further to the right?
Ow, my Dirk Niblick!
Ow, my stubbed toe!
Okay, I want to go left 1, up 2, then head right.
...Yep. Alright, let's go back and then warp to "T5" as intended.
Ow, my Mathman!
This player level truly is impressive! Alright, so the Warp Zone is next, eh? Of course, I'm sure it's not the same Warp Zone as in the main game.
That room also went well. Oh, hey! It's a dark gray dude!
Ah, well, there's my answer.
Ooh, music change. I must be in the Warp Zone proper now.
Ow, my ulna!
Ow, the same nose!
Ow, my Mr. Glitch!
Looks like another wide open area that I'll have to explore.
Wow, and they can flip too! Alright, let's follow Valso!
There we go! I'm not gonna unexpectedly warp again before hitting the warp, am I?
Verisix, eh? And he was once part of Viridian's crew?
Ow, my Fluff Noodleman!
WHAAAT?! An actual "Level Complete!" screen?! Wow, I had no idea that was possible in player levels!
...and hopefully not screw up a lot on screens that I've already completed once before.
Oh, geez. I had a total of 41 deaths today.
Hey, why didn't that work that time? I walked off the platform the same way, didn't I?

...Really? ...An emerald keycard gate? Argh... That means I'm going to have to go through all of those obstacles again later after I get the emerald keycard! Nuts. If I had known, I would've actually waited on collecting that trinket.
As expected, I'm sent here. So, I can freely warp to "T9" now, right?
Oh, wait. I came from this way. Whoops.
Yes, made it!
Yeah, we wouldn't want you screaming things like "Ow, my tibia!".
Oh, but first, a look at the map and my stats...
Ow, my legpits!
Oh, "received" is spelled correctly here.
Don't worry, Viridian. I'm sure we'll find them eventually.
Ow, the first stubbed toe again!
Oh, so those white lines are the actual Fabric of Spacetime? Wow, such impressive technology indeed!
Ow, watch that first step!
No problems there.
Whoa, that's a lot of ice. This reminds me of the room "The Voon Show" in the Final Level of the main game.
Ow, my Blackstone!
Okay, seriously. Landing on that first platform isn't hard.
Alright, there we go! And now I see a shiny that I really want! Looks like I have to approach it from the right.
Wow, I wonder who it was that saved Verisix...
I'm guessing that requires the red keycard, right?
Ow, I flipped too soon!
...What the?! I suddenly warped before I hit that warp! (I wonder if the signmaker from NakaTeleeli's Minecraft LP is present in this room...)

Man, that looks like a tricky opening to get through, like that one on the screen just above that one trinket on Golden Spiral! But at least here, I don't have to do a flawless round trip over 8 spike-filled screens!
Argh! Why did I mentally freeze there?
...Whoa, NPCs can move in player levels? I've never seen that before in other player levels!
Hello, and welcome back to VVVVVV! Let's resume Dimension Open and find out what the blue keycard does!

Okay, so last time, I downloaded the blue keycard up here. So, let's see if using it down below will unlock Valso's cell... (I have a feeling it won't, because there's only one crewmate to rescue, and this level can't be THAT short!)
Rushing into rooms that I know have spikes near the entrance is kind of a bad idea.
Easy as 3.14159% of a pie! (The other 96.85841% can go to other people, since I'm not that hungry right now.)
Will this actually work?
Also, I'm pretty sure this isn't actually "The End For Real". I do remember that there's another terminal that was asking for the blue keycard. I'm gonna warp back to "T5" now and head there.
Ow, my other stubbed toe!
Ow, my brain freeze!
Oh, the line actually did vanish! But, there's no way I'm done with the level yet, right?
D'oh! I should've disembarked when I had the chance.
Ow, my spleen!
What? Really? The Fabric of Spacetime? It must be important, because "Fabric" and "Spacetime" must be capitalized!
Typo spotted. That "recieved" should be spelled "received". ("I" before "E", except after "C".)
Well, at least I correctly remembered that this terminal was the other one that requires the blue keycard.
Ow, my nose!
To be continued... Yo!
I blame all that pain on a number of things, such as squares, and the path to the trinket near the emerald keycard gate (and also stupid mistakes on my part, of course).
Oh, man! What do we have here?
Ooh, shiny! Me wantee!
Ow, my George Frankly!
The warps are gone now...
Okay, that works.

Hmm... So, even though I've rescued Valso, this still says "One crewmate remains", because Valso wasn't rescued in the usual way for player levels. So, this level could have any number of actual duders for me to rescue!
Ow, my Fold Noodleman!
Yep. Alright, now for that trinket...
There we go! (What I did there was stop moving to the left for a split-second while falling on the right side of the line.)
Nope, I'm good... Wait, this isn't a checkmate... I can still move my king to safety this way!
Hmm... Yeah, I'd say that this room has some rotational symmetry. I don't know if it's exactly 50% though.
Let's try to line that up better, shall we?
Ow, my "...Seriously?"!
Ow, my knee!
Come on! I know I'm pressing the flip button there! It's just like when I'm certain I hit the bomb button in Touhou just as I get hit (if not sooner), and yet I die anyway!
Ow, my humerus! (Is that the funny bone?)
Ow, my Mr. Beasley!
Well, that "Arrows" room was easy.
Cool, I've unlocked another fast-travel point.
So, where else can I go without any new keycards? Find out next time!
Ow, my pupil!
I guess Valso must've removed the warps and then teleported out of here using the "T9" terminal there.
Ah, so this is that legendary Fabric of Spacetime! (I wonder what those strings in the Spacetime Container earlier were, then... Maybe they were also part of the Fabric of Spacetime?)
Yep, that warp took me back here. Alright, let's see where else I can go...
Ow, my cold feet!
Oh, man. This must be the Warp Zone.
Okay, by holding right on that conveyor, I can rest and think for a moment.
Okay, I can pass through him without triggering a "rescue", but I can't seem to speak to him again. Oh, well. Let's move on.
